      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUNEAU PETE (2) is a well performed sprinter ideally suited at the shorter trips. Last start was seventh over 515m at Launceston in a Special conditions race (30.52) but sharper trip suits this time. Is yet to taste defeat at this course and distance. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings three times from four attempts. Better than last start and worth following up. SOLD OUT (6) is mixing form lately, finishing out of the placings last time at this track but was a Grade 6 winner two back at this track. Well placed here and can atone this time. DETRIMENT (8) is in top form, scoring by 0.8 lengths (19.62) over 340m at this track and making it back to back wins. Sure to be thereabouts. WELLINGTON DEALS (1) jumps at a shorter journey and still warrants respect.",
